{
    "cells": [
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "(coherent-integration)=\n",
                "# Coherent integration"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 1,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
                "import numpy as np\n",
                "import scipy.stats\n",
                "\n",
                "import sdr\n",
                "\n",
                "%config InlineBackend.print_figure_kwargs = {\"facecolor\" : \"w\"}\n",
                "%matplotlib inline\n",
                "# %matplotlib widget\n",
                "\n",
                "sdr.plot.use_style()\n",
                "rng = np.random.default_rng(0)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "In this example, we will detect two signals, $x_1[n]$ and $x_2[n]$.\n",
                "The first signal $x_1[n]$ will be detected as is.\n",
                "The second signal $x_2[n]$ will be coherently integrated and then detected.\n",
                "\n",
                "We will show that $x_2[n]$ can have a lower SNR than $x_1[n]$ and achieve equivalent detection performance.\n",
                "The SNR reduction equals the coherent integration gain $G_c$, as calculated by {func}`sdr.coherent_gain()`."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 2,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "name": "stdout",
                    "output_type": "stream",
                    "text": [
                        "SNR 1: 10.00 dB\n",
                        "Detection false alarm rate: 1.00e-03\n",
                        "Coherently integrated samples: 15\n",
                        "Coherent gain: 11.76 dB\n",
                        "SNR 2: -1.76 dB\n"
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "snr1 = 10\n",
                "p_fa = 1e-3\n",
                "n_c = 15\n",
                "g_c = sdr.coherent_gain(n_c)\n",
                "snr2 = snr1 - g_c\n",
                "\n",
                "print(f\"SNR 1: {snr1:.2f} dB\")\n",
                "print(f\"Detection false alarm rate: {p_fa:1.2e}\")\n",
                "print(f\"Coherently integrated samples: {n_c}\")\n",
                "print(f\"Coherent gain: {g_c:.2f} dB\")\n",
                "print(f\"SNR 2: {snr2:.2f} dB\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Detect $x_1[n]$\n",
                "\n",
                "The complex time-domain signal $x_1[n]$ is the sum of a phase-coherent signal and noise.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$x_1[n] = s_1[n] + w_1[n]$$\n",
                "\n",
                "The signal $s_1[n]$ has constant amplitude $A_1$.\n",
                "The noise $w_1[n]$ is i.i.d. complex additive white Gaussian with variance $\\sigma_1^2$.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$s_1[n] = A_1$$\n",
                "$$w_1[n] \\sim \\mathcal{CN}(0, \\sigma_1^2)$$"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 3,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "def create_x(snr):\n",
                "    sigma = 1  # Noise standard deviation, sigma\n",
                "    A = np.sqrt(sdr.linear(snr) * sigma**2)  # Signal voltage, A\n",
                "\n",
                "    n = 100_000\n",
                "    s = A * np.ones(n)\n",
                "    w = rng.normal(0, np.sqrt(sigma**2 / 2), n) + 1j * rng.normal(0, np.sqrt(sigma**2 / 2), n)\n",
                "    x_h0 = w  # x under the H0 hypothesis\n",
                "    x_h1 = s + w  # x under the H1 hypothesis\n",
                "\n",
                "    return A, sigma, x_h0, x_h1"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Generate the complex time-domain signal $x_1[n]$ with 10-dB SNR."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 4,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "A1, sigma1, x1_h0, x1_h1 = create_x(snr1)\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(x1_h0.real, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(x1_h1.real, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"$\\mathrm{{Re}}\\{{x_1[n]\\}}$ with {snr1}-dB SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "The signal $x_1[n]$ is distributed as follows.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$\n",
                "\\begin{align}\n",
                "    \\mathcal{H}_0 &: x_1[n] \\sim \\mathcal{CN}(0, \\sigma_1^2) \\\\\n",
                "    \\mathcal{H}_1 &: x_1[n] \\sim \\mathcal{CN}(A_1, \\sigma_1^2)\n",
                "\\end{align}\n",
                "$$\n",
                "\n",
                "$\\mathcal{H}_0$ is the null hypothesis.\n",
                "It indicates the condition when only noise is present.\n",
                "$\\mathcal{H}_1$ is the alternative hypothesis.\n",
                "It indicates the condition when signal and noise are present."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 5,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "x1_h0_real_theory = scipy.stats.norm(0, np.sqrt(sigma1**2 / 2))\n",
                "x1_h1_real_theory = scipy.stats.norm(A1, np.sqrt(sigma1**2 / 2))\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "plt.hist(x1_h0.real, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.hist(x1_h1.real, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "axis = np.linspace(min(x1_h0.real), max(x1_h1.real), 101)\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, x1_h0_real_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, x1_h1_real_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.legend()\n",
                "plt.xlabel(\"$\\mathrm{Re}\\{x_1[n]\\}$\")\n",
                "plt.ylabel(\"Probability density\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"PDF of $\\mathrm{{Re}}\\{{x_1[n]\\}}$ with {snr1}-dB SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Determine the detection performance of $x_1[n]$.\n",
                "If the absolute phase of $x_1[n]$ is unknown, which is common, the signal must be detected by examining the power of the signal $z_1[n]$.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$z_1[n] = \\left| x_1[n] \\right|^2$$"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 6,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "z1_h0 = np.abs(x1_h0) ** 2\n",
                "z1_h1 = np.abs(x1_h1) ** 2\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(z1_h0, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(z1_h1, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"$z_1[n]$ with {snr1}-dB SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "The signal power $z_1[n]$ is distributed as follows.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$\n",
                "\\begin{align}\n",
                "    \\mathcal{H}_0 &: z_1[n] \\sim \\chi_{\\nu}^2 \\\\\n",
                "    \\mathcal{H}_1 &: z_1[n] \\sim {\\chi'}_{\\nu}^2(\\lambda)\n",
                "\\end{align}\n",
                "$$\n",
                "\n",
                "$\\nu$ is the degrees of freedom and $\\lambda$ is the non-centrality parameter.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$\\nu = 2$$\n",
                "$$\\lambda = \\frac{A_1^2}{\\sigma_1^2 / 2}$$"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 7,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "nu = 2  # Degrees of freedom\n",
                "lambda_ = A1**2 / (sigma1**2 / 2)  # Non-centrality parameter\n",
                "z1_h0_theory = scipy.stats.chi2(nu, scale=sigma1**2 / 2)\n",
                "z1_h1_theory = scipy.stats.ncx2(nu, lambda_, scale=sigma1**2 / 2)\n",
                "\n",
                "threshold = z1_h0_theory.isf(p_fa)\n",
                "p_d = z1_h1_theory.sf(threshold)\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "plt.hist(z1_h0, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.hist(z1_h1, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "axis = np.linspace(min(z1_h0), max(z1_h1), 101)\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, z1_h0_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, z1_h1_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.axvline(threshold, color=\"k\", linestyle=\"--\", label=\"Threshold\")\n",
                "plt.legend()\n",
                "plt.xlabel(\"$z_1[n]$\")\n",
                "plt.ylabel(\"Probability density\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"PDF of $z_1[n]$ with {snr1}-dB SNR\\n$P_d =$ {p_d:1.2e}, $P_{{fa}} =$ {p_fa:1.2e}\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Measure the probability of detection and probability of false alarm.\n",
                "Compare the empirical results to theoretical."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 8,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "name": "stdout",
                    "output_type": "stream",
                    "text": [
                        "Probability of detection: 8.10e-01 theory, 8.11e-01 measured\n",
                        "Probability of false alarm: 1.00e-03 theory, 1.05e-03 measured\n"
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "p_d_meas = np.mean(z1_h1 > threshold)\n",
                "print(f\"Probability of detection: {p_d:1.2e} theory, {p_d_meas:1.2e} measured\")\n",
                "\n",
                "p_fa_meas = np.mean(z1_h0 > threshold)\n",
                "print(f\"Probability of false alarm: {p_fa:1.2e} theory, {p_fa_meas:1.2e} measured\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Detect $x_2[n]$\n",
                "\n",
                "Generate the complex time-domain signal $x_2[n]$ with -1.76-dB SNR."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 9,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "A2, sigma2, x2_h0, x2_h1 = create_x(snr2)\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(x2_h0.real, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(x2_h1.real, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"$\\mathrm{{Re}}\\{{x_2[n]\\}}$ with {snr2:1.2f}-dB SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 10,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "x2_h0_real_theory = scipy.stats.norm(0, np.sqrt(sigma2**2 / 2))\n",
                "x2_h1_real_theory = scipy.stats.norm(A2, np.sqrt(sigma2**2 / 2))\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "plt.hist(x2_h0.real, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.hist(x2_h1.real, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "axis = np.linspace(min(x2_h0.real), max(x2_h1.real), 101)\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, x2_h0_real_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, x2_h1_real_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.legend()\n",
                "plt.xlabel(\"$\\mathrm{Re}\\{x_2[n]\\}$\")\n",
                "plt.ylabel(\"Probability density\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"PDF of $\\mathrm{{Re}}\\{{x_2[n]\\}}$ with {snr2:1.2f}-dB SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Coherently integrate $N_C$ contiguous samples from the signal $x_2[n]$.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$y_2[n] = \\sum_{m=0}^{N_C-1} x_2[n -m]$$"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 11,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "y2_h0 = np.sum(np.lib.stride_tricks.sliding_window_view(x2_h0, n_c), axis=-1)\n",
                "y2_h1 = np.sum(np.lib.stride_tricks.sliding_window_view(x2_h1, n_c), axis=-1)\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(y2_h0.real, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(y2_h1.real, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"$\\mathrm{{Re}}\\{{y_2[n]\\}}$ with {snr2:0.2f}-dB initial SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "The coherently integrated signal $y_2[n]$ is distributed as follows.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$\n",
                "\\begin{align}\n",
                "    \\mathcal{H}_0 &: y_2[n] \\sim \\mathcal{CN}(0, N_C \\sigma_2^2) \\\\\n",
                "    \\mathcal{H}_1 &: y_2[n] \\sim \\mathcal{CN}(N_C A_2, N_C \\sigma_2^2)\n",
                "\\end{align}\n",
                "$$"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 12,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "y2_h0_real_theory = scipy.stats.norm(0, np.sqrt(n_c * sigma2**2 / 2))\n",
                "y2_h1_real_theory = scipy.stats.norm(n_c * A2, np.sqrt(n_c * sigma2**2 / 2))\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "plt.hist(y2_h0.real, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.hist(y2_h1.real, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "axis = np.linspace(min(y2_h0.real), max(y2_h1.real), 101)\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, y2_h0_real_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, y2_h1_real_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.legend()\n",
                "plt.xlabel(\"$\\mathrm{Re}\\{y_2[n]\\}$\")\n",
                "plt.ylabel(\"Probability density\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"$\\mathrm{{Re}}\\{{y_2[n]\\}}$ with {snr2:1.2f}-dB initial SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Similarly, determine the detection performance of $y_2[n]$.\n",
                "If the phase of $y_2[n]$ is unknown, the signal must be detected by examining the power of the signal $z_2[n]$.\n",
                "\n",
                "$$z_2[n] = \\left| y_2[n] \\right|^2$$"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 13,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "z2_h0 = np.abs(y2_h0) ** 2\n",
                "z2_h1 = np.abs(y2_h1) ** 2\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(z2_h0, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.time_domain(z2_h1, label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"$z_2[n]$ with {snr2:1.2f}-dB initial SNR\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 14,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "nu = 2  # Degrees of freedom\n",
                "lambda_ = A2**2 * n_c / (sigma2**2 / 2)  # Non-centrality parameter\n",
                "z2_h0_theory = scipy.stats.chi2(nu, scale=n_c * sigma2**2 / 2)\n",
                "z2_h1_theory = scipy.stats.ncx2(nu, lambda_, scale=n_c * sigma2**2 / 2)\n",
                "\n",
                "threshold = z2_h0_theory.isf(p_fa)\n",
                "p_d = z2_h1_theory.sf(threshold)\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "plt.hist(z2_h0, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.hist(z2_h1, bins=101, histtype=\"step\", density=True)\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "axis = np.linspace(min(z2_h0), max(z2_h1), 101)\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, z2_h0_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_0$: Noise\")\n",
                "plt.plot(axis, z2_h1_theory.pdf(axis), label=\"$\\mathcal{H}_1$: Signal + Noise\")\n",
                "plt.axvline(threshold, color=\"k\", linestyle=\"--\", label=\"Threshold\")\n",
                "plt.legend()\n",
                "plt.xlabel(\"$z_2[n]$\")\n",
                "plt.ylabel(\"Probability density\")\n",
                "plt.title(f\"PDF of $z_2[n]$ with {snr2:1.2f}-dB initial SNR\\n$P_d =$ {p_d:1.2e}, $P_{{fa}} =$ {p_fa:1.2e}\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Measure the probability of detection and probability of false alarm.\n",
                "Compare the empirical results to theoretical.\n",
                "\n",
                "Notice that the detection performance of $x_1[n]$ and $x_2[n]$ are equivalent."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 15,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "name": "stdout",
                    "output_type": "stream",
                    "text": [
                        "Probability of detection: 8.10e-01 theory, 8.11e-01 measured\n",
                        "Probability of false alarm: 1.00e-03 theory, 1.05e-03 measured\n"
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "p_d_meas = np.mean(z2_h1 > threshold)\n",
                "print(f\"Probability of detection: {p_d:1.2e} theory, {p_d_meas:1.2e} measured\")\n",
                "\n",
                "p_fa_meas = np.mean(z2_h0 > threshold)\n",
                "print(f\"Probability of false alarm: {p_fa:1.2e} theory, {p_fa_meas:1.2e} measured\")"
            ]
        }
    ],
